<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-28T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-28T15:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">704.2523: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-28T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            28, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November 29, 1.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Minister of Foreign Affairs requested me today to ask that United
                                States consular officers in Peru be placed in charge of Chilean
                                consular interests. Instructions desired. Strongly urge that this be
                                done if consistent with policy.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>